            <!-- Contents -->
            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">Treatise consisting of succinct definitions of 199 commonly used technical Sufi terms. There are three different versions of the text (see below). The first part is based on Qushayrī’s definitions in his Risāla.</note>
               <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
               <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">A much copied work, verified by at least seven historic mss. However, there are three verifiable versions of the original text: version A in Damascus (begins with waqt), without introduction, copied by Ayyūb b. Badr (see Manisa 1183, c. 650H), version B in Konya in a different order (begins with hājis), with an introduction, which was written in Malatya in 615H (see Milli 571, 668H), and version C which was included in the FM (II 128–34; Chapter 173, the response to al-Tirmidhī’s question 153), and consists of version B in reverse order with added questions linking each term.</note>
